HEADWORD: Concrescible
<hw>Con*cres"ci*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>Capable of being changed from a liquid to a solid state.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They formed a . . . fixed <qex>concrescible</qex> oil.</q>
<rj><qau>Fourcroy (Trans. ).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concrescive</ent>⟦br⟧
